Picking up a pizza from here is a pain because they know they make less money. They'd much rather you pay more for the food, not get any discount for picking it up, also pay a "delivery fee", and tip the guy who brings you your pizza (half-cold by the way). I've gotten on airplanes with less hassle than picking up a pizza from here. Also, delivery timing is mediocre. Maybe a block or two away, they still manage to bring lukewarm food. And I love Papa John's as a company. Love their pizza. But if the pizza could be edible when it comes from here and/or the lady at the register could relax a bit when people pick-up, that would be nice.

DO NOT ORDER FROM THIS PAPA JOHN'S. I ordered one evening for a group of people the total was around $60, I had put it on my credit card and the delivery man told me that my credit card had been declined. I believed the man (which now I realize I shouldn't have), I ended up paying cash for the pizza AND being charged on my card! I called the next day and the manager told me that my card was never charged, yet my bank verified that they did in fact charge my card. I realize now that the manager of this Papa johns must be in on this trick .. and from the looks of it I can see that other reviewers have had similar experiences. I'm planning on not only reporting this to corporate but to the local police because it is despicable. Moral of the story: GET YOUR PIZZA ELSEWHERE, THESE PEOPLE ARE CROOKS.
